  "instructions": [
    "In a large Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and sauté for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the smoked duck legs and cook for 5 minutes on each side, until browned.",
    "Add the chopped parsley, dill, bay leaves, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Pour in the red wine vinegar and chicken broth, and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and let the stew simmer for 20 minutes, or until the duck is tender.",
    "Remove the bay leaves and serve the stew hot, garnished with additional parsley and dill if desired."
